    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_5DB20D1E-6EDF-4CA6-8DF3-870D5B9239C9" class="text-block-content">
    <p>If Discussions Redesign is enabled by your institution, <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-report-a-reply-in-a-discussion-in-Discussions-Redesign/ta-p/542169" target="_blank">users can report replies</a> from the Discussions page by default. </p>
<p>Users can report replies by clicking the Options icon for the reply and clicking the Report link. When a reply is reported by a user, the user must indicate why the reply is being reported (inappropriate, offensive and/or abusive, or other). Reporting a reply cannot be undone. </p>
<p>Discussions Redesign is currently a beta feature. Some discussion settings and features in the classic Discussions interface may not function or be available in Discussions Redesign. </p>
<p><strong>Notes: </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>If Discussions Redesign is not available in your course, it has not been enabled by your institution.</li>
<li>If a student creates a discussion that includes a file, the file will be added to the unfiled folder in course files.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_discussions" data-step-uuid="22D29CF9-7156-44CB-B41A-2C39974676E0">
